your Google Ads. Instead, set realistic expectations for your conversion rates based on your industry and specific business goals.<\/li>\n<li>Make sure your landing page is relevant, engaging, and user-friendly, with a clear call to action that matches your ad&#8217;s message. There is nothing worse than clicking on an interesting ad only to be taken to a landing page where you can\u2019t find the item that interested you.<\/li>\n<li>Develop a strong brand identity that resonates with your target audience and inspires trust and recognition. You want people to recognize your brand when they see your ads.<\/li>\n<li>Use ad extensions, which are small pieces of information that you can show next to your ad. These may include website links, pricing information or other kinds of information. Ad extensions can increase the chances someone will click on your ad.<\/li>\n<li>Use negative keywords to filter out irrelevant traffic and focus on the right audience, which can increase your conversion rate. For example, if you have a pizza restaurant, you might want to filter out \u201cpizza recipes\u201d so you don\u2019t get traffic from people just researching how to make pizza at home.<\/li>\n<li>Improve your landing page load speed. A slow loading landing page can frustrate users and cause them to abandon your site, resulting in lower conversions. Make sure your landing page loads quickly.<\/li>\n<li>Schedule your Google Ads so they are shown only at certain times of the day or week, which can help you reach your target audience more effectively.<\/li>\n<li>Become adept at Google Ads\u2019 options for targeting your audience. This includes demographic targeting and affinity targeting, which can help you reach the right audience for your business.<\/li>\n<li>Use ad rotation, which will enable you to test different ad variations to see which ones perform best. This can help you to constantly improve your conversion rate over time.<\/li>\n<li>Use location-based targeting which allows you to show your ads to users in specific geographic locations. This can help you reach your target audience more effectively. It\u2019s crucial for a local business.<\/li>\n<li>Use A\/B testing to test variations of your ad. Test headline, body copy, images and landing pages. A\/B testing enables you to identify which ads perform best. You can then improve your conversion rate over time.<\/li>\n<li>Use call tracking as well as tracking online track phone calls generated by your Google Ads. This is another way to help measure the effectiveness of your campaigns and optimize them for better results.<\/li>\n<li>Use ad placement targeting to show your ads on specific websites or placements, which can help you reach your target audience more effectively.<\/li>\n<li>Consider using ad frequency capping to limit the number of times your ads are shown to a user, which can prevent ad fatigue and improve your conversion rate.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p><strong>Expert Help to Run Your Google Ads Campaigns<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>There is a lot to creating, testing, tweaking and running effective Google Ads campaigns. You are already busy running your business, and may not have the time or inclination of getting into the nitty gritty of Google Ads.<\/p>\n<p>That doesn\u2019t mean you should miss out. If you need help improving your Google Ads and boosting your conversions, Umbrella Local is here to offer a free consultation and expert advice.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/umbrellaxact.com\/contact-us\/\">Contact Umbrella Local Experts here<\/a> to schedule a free consultation or call (646) 440-1426 to discuss increasing Google Ads conversions for your business.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Everyone wants their audience to click on their Google Ads and eventually buy. There are many things you can do to increase your Google Ads conversions. Here are 21 of them. &nbsp; Make sure you understand your target audience and their needs. Continuously analyze your data to 